description.narrative: UNICEF supported governments in 17 states to strengthen child protection workforce for improved prevention and response services to 350,500 vulnerable children. In 10 states, UNICEF strengthened capacities of responders for providing healing and recovery services to 33,189 child survivors of violence and abuse. 133,370 children received psychosocial care through UNICEF supported safe spaces in three states during emergencies. 1,023 Special Courts for trial of child sexual abuse cases were supported through advocacy, design and capacity development by UNICEF. Partnership with Supreme Court and High Courts supported the acceleration of child care reform and the strengthening of standards of alternative care | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2020
